UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2213
1 A RESOLUTION commemorating the 80th Southern Legislative Conference of the
2 Council of State Governments Southern Office.
3 WHEREAS, the Council of State Governments, CSG South, is a nonpartisan,
4 nonprofit member organization that serves the Southern legislatures of Alabama,
5 Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, Missouri, North Carolina,
6 Oklahoma, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, and West Virginia; and
7 WHEREAS, with regionally based state leadership and perspective, and national-
8 level resources, CSG South provides Southern legislators and government staff with a
9 wide variety of programs and services that facilitate regional cooperation and encourage
10 the exchange of information; and
11 WHEREAS, the mission of the organization is to serve as a community of the
12 states, committed to connecting, informing, inspiring, and empowering public servants in
13 all three branches of state government to put the best ideas and solutions into practice;
14 and
15 WHEREAS, in pursuit of this mission, CSG South has convened the Southern
16 Legislative Conference for the past 79 years, with decades of fellowship and cooperation
17 among the 15 Southern states; and
18 WHEREAS, the 80th Southern Legislative Conference will convene in Lexington,
19 Kentucky, from July 11 to 15, 2026; and
20 WHEREAS, more than 1,500 Southern legislators, government staff, and their
21 families will gather to discuss policy matters specifically affecting Southern states to
22 bridge commonalities and discuss solutions for current policy trends, challenges, and
23 opportunities;
24 NOW, THEREFORE,
25 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
26 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
27 Section 1. The members of the House of Representatives highlight and
